A week after discovering an interim deal, both banks explained that MUFG was going to buy 9.9% of Morgan Stanley common shares at the unit price of $25.25, or an amount of $3 billion.
The agreed price is less than 19 % of the book value of the securities as at 31 August.
MUFG will invest an additional $6 billion with the purchase of convertible securities which will ensure a 10% return and a conversion price of $31.25.
Morgan Stanley said the global transaction would be based on a price per unit of measure of $29, or 28% above its current exchange rate.
Morgan Stanley was down 6.79% at $23.07 each at 17:00 GMT.
“This strategic alliance constitutes an important opportunity to accelerate Morgan Stanley’s transition to the status of a banking holding company,” said Juan Mack, CEO of the American group.
Morgan Stanley adopted this new statute last week, which would have to allow it to diversify its activities but it passes under the authority of the Federal Reserve.
Its alliance with MUFG also confirms that the current financial crisis is forcing Wall Street’s biggest names to behave much more prudently than before.
The modalities presented last Monday also show that the deal has been modified during the last days: last Monday, Morgan had announced that it would sell up to 20% of its shares to Japanese for almost $ 8.5 billion.
"A week ago," explained Toshihide Mizuno, the executive director of MUFG in Tokyo, "we thought that the stake would have been composed only of ordinary shares.
But in view of the current economic and market situation, we have wished to minimize the risks and cover ourselves.”
Based on the weighted average price, MUFG will pay its Morgan Stanley securities 7% below its book value.
And the transaction will result in a dilution of about 20% of earnings per share.
The agreement stipulates that MUFG will be able to convert within one year half of its preferred shares into ordinary shares if these shares are sold at more than 50% above the conversion price, i.e. at $47 or less, during a given period.
Morgan Stanley assures that the capital provided by MUFG will allow it to seize investment opportunities, strengthen its balance sheet and increase its liquidity.
A spokeswoman for the group declined to elaborate on the strategic plans of the two new allies.
Following MUFG’s investment, Morgan Stanley should show a Tier One solvency ratio of close to 15%, one of the best in the industry.
Morgan said it had greatly eased its balance since the end of August.
The last few weeks were exhausting for the group, which saw its stock market price fall in half as the cost of security against a risk of defects on its debt took off.
This cost was falling last Monday but remained at a high level, around 12%.
Last week, Goldman Sachs, the other single “survivor” of the big Wall Street investment banks following the bankruptcies of Bear Stearns and Lehman Brothers and the purchase of Merrill Lynch, announced it had raised $15 billion, in part for Berkshire Hathaway, Warren Buffett’s group.
Rafael Correa in Quito, this Monday.
To refound the republic around the socialism of the 21st century.
This is the joint project of Venezuelan Hugo Chavez, Bolivian Evo Morales and Ecuadorian Rafael Correa.
This Sunday, following the example of his colleagues and friends, is the third to put to the vote a draft for a new Constitution.
Mission accomplished since 64% of voters voted "yes" to the referendum, according to official results that referred to 80% of the votes.
According to these results, the "no" obtained 28%, 7% of the votes were null votes and 0.7% were blank votes.
In order for the draft Constitution to be adopted, it had to obtain half of the votes plus one.
On Sunday, two polls conducted at the exit of the polling stations and a recount by a non-governmental organization had announced a broad victory to the “yes”, estimating it between 63% and 70%.
Rafael Correa had also claimed on the night of Sunday to Monday the victory of his draft Constitution.
The "Constitution triumphed overwhelmingly," he had assured, congratulating Ecuadorians who head the government of Guayaquil, 280 kilometers southwest of Quito.
Thus, Rafael Correa has been congratulated by Chávez and Morales but also by his Chilean colleague Micaela Bachelet.
The elections, which will take place in full calm, according to the observation mission of the Organization of American States (OAS), referred to a text of 444 points that consolidated the " new socialism " advocated by the President.
The draft Constitution entailed an increase in the power of the State over the economy, reserving for it the " development planning " of a country which lived essentially on the extraction of oil by foreign companies and on the foreign currencies sent by its emigrants.
Led by Correa, elected in 2006, the bill also grants the head of state reinforced powers, which can serve up to two consecutive terms of four years each and will have the possibility of dissolving the Assembly.
Correa already announced that he would use this power and seek a new mandate in February 2009.
The Constitution also consolidates the principle of free health and education services that the President began to establish in this country of 13.9 million inhabitants, in which 50% of the population lives below the poverty line.
It finally foresees the prohibition of the presence of foreign troops, which will put an end to the agreement between Quito and Washington for the use of an Ecuadorian base as a starting point for American anti-drug operations.
The 19 kidnapped people have been released in Chad
An Egyptian commando launched the assault against the kidnappers of the eleven tourists and their eight companions captured ten days ago.
They're in Cairo.
The eleven European tourists and their eight Egyptian companions kidnapped ten days ago in the desert arrived unharmed in the Egyptian capital after being released Monday afternoon.
In the morning, they had been released by Egyptian special forces in Chad.
They all looked good when they arrived at 3:30 p.m. aboard a special plane at the Al Maza military base, adjacent to Cairo’s international airport.
Helicopters immediately transported them to the hospital in Maadi, a residential suburb of Cairo, for medical testing, so they have not been able to speak to the press.
"They are in good health" and "no ransom was paid" to the kidnappers, Egyptian Tourism Minister Zoheir Garana said at the airport.
On September 19, these hostages fell into the hands of 35 unknown kidnappers while enjoying an off-road safari in a desert area at the foot of Mount Ouanat, on the borders of Egypt, Sudan and Libya, and have since moved from one zulo to another.
The group consisted of eleven tourists - five Italians, five Germans and one Romanian - and eight Egyptians: two guides, four drivers, a border guard and the director of the travel agency Aegyptous, in charge of the organization of the safari.
An Egyptian security official said 30 members of the special forces, transported aboard two helicopters, had launched the assault during the night before dawn.
"An exchange of gunfire occurred, and they killed half of the kidnappers, the others have fled," said this official who kept the anonymity.
According to him, 150 members of the Egyptian special forces of the "lightning" unit were sent to Sudan, where they had the support of German and Italian commandos.
Italian Foreign Minister Franco Frattini mentioned in Belgrade the role played by secret agents and members of Italian special forces.
"We must recognize that we have achieved this result thanks to the professionalism and effectiveness of our men of the secret services, of the special forces," he said without going into details.
He also denied paying a ransom.
On the eve, the Sudanese army claimed to have intercepted during a patrol an off-road vehicle on which the kidnappers were on board, killing six of them, including the Chadian chief, and detaining two.
It also claimed that they were related to a rebel group in Darfur, the Sudan Liberation Movement-Unit (SLA-U), a claim immediately denied by this group.
Letters - Silent majority of culture
A debate about the financing of culture has made headlines and occupies the current election campaign.
It's better that way.
But a sector of our cultural life is always forgotten.
Who will stand up to denounce the miserable sums given to small museums, archives, archaeological excavations or national historical sites that are starving?
What politician will dare to remind the federal government to neglect its monuments and heritage buildings?
Why don’t we have real laws that effectively preserve our heritage like in Canada and Quebec?
Did you know that the French government spends three and a half million euros to restore only the castle of Chinon in the Loire Valley?
In the United States, it is written in your Constitution that the protection of heritage is part of the culture of Americans and that this heritage has to be protected by all citizens, all elected and all government departments, and all of this, in concert.
In Quebec, in the Quebec Federation of History Societies, at least 40,000 benevolent people grouped into 211 societies of history, heritage, archives and genealogy are concerned with searching history, preserving with little money heaps of private archives and preserving archaeological remains.
These are often the watchdogs of our heritage, who protest with energy and despair when promoters and managers throw their bulldozers at our old stones and forgotten cemeteries.
For when, a monument to history and heritage?
The governments of the Netherlands nationalize a portion of Fortis Bank.
The states of the Netherlands - being the first in Europe - will help with a nationalization of the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis that is in trouble due to the effect of the mortgage crisis of the North American market: the three countries will support in total with 11.2 billion euros this financial and insurance institution that also has businesses in Hungary.
This weekend the governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands held higher-level consultations with the President of the European Central Bank and the European Commission’s Head of Economic Competition.
The Fortis Bank is the first to suffer the crisis of the Eurozone in the framework of the international financial crisis that has been occurring in several waves more than a year ago, therefore the decisions taken with regard to the Bank, in a certain sense can be considered as precedents.
According to the decision taken early on Sunday, the three states will buy about half (49 percent) of the property owned by the Bank in their area.
The Bank will surely sell a part of its business, among them mainly the activities -mainly insurance- bought last year from the Dutch ABN Amró.
Fortis shares began a sharp decline last week and by the second half of the week there were already important signs of crisis in the institution.
However, analysts agree that with its 85,000 employees this bank is too big to allow it to fail.
The company’s shares fell 12 percent on Friday alone, the lowest point in 14 years.
Since January, the value of shares has declined by more than two-thirds.
Looking at the current share prices, the total value of the group’s capital in the market is around 14 billion euros, but according to the company’s executives this is not real.
The Bank’s management blamed the sharp drop in Fortis shares on the insecurities of the U.S. market in relation to the approval of the $700 billion U.S. package plan.
On Monday, the shares showed a slight increase.
On Friday, Filip Dierckx was appointed as the bank’s new chief executive.
The Bank also sought private investors, but so far no one has given a concrete offer.
The Belgian government had previously assured investors that they did not have to worry, they were not going to lose their money.
No panic has occurred among the Bank’s clients so far, they did not invade the bank offices to withdraw their money.
Fortis has its own branch in Hungary and has also purchased leasing companies.
Fox in the chicken coop
In the United States, life and health insurance companies often refuse to sign an insurance contract when they see the data on the purchase of medicine.
Privacy policy specialists fear that the market for personal data will become uncontrollable.
"There are programs for the protection of personal data, which to the use of the data of the prescriptions in all cases binds it to the approval of the given person.
It must be in independent hands, because otherwise, “we trust the fox the chicken coop” – quotes the Washington Post Richard Dick, designer of the prescription tracking program.
Insurance companies make the price of the insurance and the amount of compensation depend on the health status of the client and if they believe the risk is excessive, they simply do not make the contract.
Before they sent the client to medical check-up and signed the contract with him already knowing the result of the check-up.
Dick invented a much cheaper procedure ten years ago: with the customer identification number he easily gets from pharmacies the list of drugs purchased in the last year and a half and the program itself draws the conclusion about the illnesses and health status of the customer.
For example, if you systematically take large doses of cholesterol-lowering pills, it indicates that the level of fat in your blood is practically incurably high, so you are immediately included in a higher risk category.
Numerous versions of the program circulate, some even set a risk number, so the insurance company in addition to the administration has barely anything to do, although there are small difficulties in this regard.
Among the disadvantages of the program is for example that some drugs are multi-purpose, for example certain substances serve both to treat headaches and heat waves and even as antidepressants.
The latter is a major risk-increasing factor for insurance companies while the former do not.
Special companies were set up to consult and process these data, which, before acquiring the necessary information from pharmacies, require the patient's approval.
The authorities are already forcing them to do so, although they have not received a fine for negligence so far.
Some companies have also recently compiled the results of laboratory exams and combined with drug consumption data, they obtain more accurate information about the patient’s health status.
More and more companies have access to this data and simultaneously it is increasingly difficult to control its use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those providing health services.
The bill that gives the right to the authority to control specialized companies for the provision of personal data is already before Congress.
Dick Richard acknowledges that this is insufficient: therefore he developed his program, which will require the specific approval of the person for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another matter that such a person cannot deny his approval, because otherwise the insurance companies will not sign the contract with him.
So hens, despite everything, are exposed to the fox’s goodwill.
Global menu of Marseille
The European Union doubles its trade with India
As the European Union and India are reciprocal trading partners, this issue in addition to the other mostly global issues dominated the agenda of the ninth summit.
A Franco-Indian summit will also be held today, focusing on cooperation in nuclear energy.
Although the European Union recognizes that India is a major developing democratic power that should have more voice and vote in international affairs, member countries have yet to come to a common denominator on whether they should support New Delhi as a permanent member of the UN Security Council.
This issue has not been addressed at the ninth summit started yesterday in Marseille.
French President Nicolas Sarkozy, EU President-in-Office, José Manuel Barroso, Commission President, and Javier Solana, Chief Foreign Policy Representative, received Manmohan Singh, Prime Minister of India, with whom they reached an agreement to double in five years, i.e. increase to more than one hundred billion euros, their trade.
Given that between 2000 and 2007 the exchange of goods increased from 25 billion to 55 billion, this is not an overly ambitious goal.
In this way, the twenty-six existing bilateral civil aviation agreements with India were legally harmonised, so that air transport could also fly in the future.
India wants to sign a free trade agreement with the EU by the end of 2009.
Sarkozy promised to speed up the negotiations.
The objective is balance, because while the EU is India’s first trading partner, New Delhi is only in ninth place among the EU’s trading partners.
The summit paid attention to global affairs.
Both sides condemned the Afghan and Pakistani situation and terrorism - all forms of the latter - and urged the convening of a UN conference.
The conclusion of the Doha trade liberalization round was also urged, although both sides bear great responsibility for its failure.
The EU has confirmed that it will stick to its energy and climate programme, i.e. by 2020 it wants to reduce polluting emissions by at least twenty percent.
India also agrees with this, just as at next year’s climate conference a global agreement should be reached and production of greenhouse gases should be cut by 50 percent by 2050.
They also wished to hinder the rise in food prices and supported the convening of an international conference to review the financial crisis.
Today the head of government of India will travel to the French capital, where - in a bilateral meeting - he will sign an agreement on the peaceful use of nuclear energy.
Paris is confident that French companies will receive orders worth 20 billion euros to build nuclear reactors.
According to news agency reports, the deal would be for a period of 15 years.
In Frankfurt more than three hundred Italian publishers
Strong presence of Italian publishers at the international exhibition of the Frankfurt book.
More than 300 Italian publishers will be present at the 60th edition of Buchmesse, the most important international meeting for the exchange of rights.
The international exhibition of the Frankfurt book expects for this edition more than 7 thousand exhibitors from 102 different countries who will occupy the 171,790 square meters of the exhibition with more than 403,000 titles on display and with Turkey as guest of honor.
It will be the undersecretary of the Ministry of cultural goods and activities Francisco Maria Giro to represent the Italian government in the ceremony of inauguration of the Italian pavilion: Italy will be institutionally and effectively present with a point Italy - 264 square meters of exhibition space.
An encounter with the print will follow at the Room Struktur in Hall 5.0 of the Buchmesse: this will be the occasion to present figures, trends and prospects on the state of publishing in Italy.
According to the data, the weight of books by foreign authors decreases progressively over the total Italian production, and in particular that for adults and adolescents.
Steve Fossett's plane found missing a year ago
The wreckage of the plane of Steve Fossett, the millionaire who disappeared on September 3, 2007 while flying over the Nevada desert, has been found.
The debris was found on a 3,000-meter high plateau in the Mammoth Lakes area of the Nevada Mountains on the California-Nevada border.
Inside the plane, there were no human remains.
Wood County Commissioner John Anderson said: "The plane has been located, we have sent a squadron, and now we have confirmation that this is exactly what Steve Fossett was flying on the day of his disappearance."
No human remains have been found in or around the plane.
The 63-year-old millionaire was reported dead in February.
The American office for the safety of transports (Ntsb) has announced that a few hours after the sighting of the remains, a squadron of investigators has been sent to identify the device: it is the Bellanca 8kcab, dispersed since September 3, 2007, when Fossett took off from Yerington in Nevada for a three-hour flight.
Yesterday, also in California, not far from the Nevada border, some personal remains of Fossett have been found by a couple near their Mammoth Lakes home.
These are two documents with the name of Fossett, the two issued by the Federal Aviation Administration of Illinois, cash and a sweatshirt.
Fossett's search had been interrupted a month after his disappearance.
The millionaire had conquered a place in history thanks to a long series of firsts.
In 2002, at the sixth attempt, he had become the first Man to complete the world’s spin in a hot air balloon: two lonely weeks of flying.
Three years later he had made the round the world by plane and without stopovers.
Among his records, also that for having flown at 15,445 meters above the Andes, but with a co-pilot.
Glk, the advertising you don't expect
An out-of-schemes SUV with an original and well-established design with defined lines and determined angles.
It is this, in short, Glk the last born among the "compact" off-road vans of the star house with which Mercedes-Benz has sought to give a window of novelty in this sector.
Own by the content outside the traditional, it will be unexpected and unconventional, the communication that will accompany the launch of the Glk SUV, available in the Mercedes-Benz showrooms from October 17.
The advertising campaign that accompanied the debut of the new car will launch an unprecedented mode of communication through a 3D advertising campaign, used for the first time in Italy by a car brand.
A project with maxi-posters, articulated in three different phases, that will dominate the central street of the Milanese shopping, avenue Como, until November 15.
The first phase of this new type of communication will begin with the presentation of the car in stereoscopic version and thanks to special glasses distributed on the avenue As it will be possible to see the new SUV in almost real dimensions and in three-dimensional format.
Indeed, looking at the images you will have the impression that the car comes out outside the poster.
Subsequently, through the use of the innovative technology Elumina8 the new Glk will be illuminated at different times in all its details, to be recomposed into a single image.
Undoubtedly Mercedes with this advertisement is trying to introduce something new into the stereotype of automotive communication.
Will this formula be able to capture the interest of future buyers? we will see.
